conn.commit()

import shlex
import subprocess

def execute_command(command):
    if ">" in command:
        command = shlex.split(command)

        redirect_index = command.index(">")

        filename = command[redirect_index + 1]

        command = command[:redirect_index]

        command.extend(["|", "python", f">{filename}"])

    result = subprocess.run(command, shell=True, capture_output=True)

    return result

if __name__ == '__main__':
    command = "python ./test.py > output.txt"
    result = execute_command(command)

    print(f"Command '{command}' returned with status {result.returncode}")
    print(f"Output: {result.stdout}")
